*Galax urceolata* (Poiret) Brummitt

Locally abundant on bank of *Sphagnum*-rich portion 
of "Swan Fork" ravine and on adjacent N-facing slope,
near where "Swan Fork" crosses CCC trail about 0.2 mi.
E of Strawberry Plains Rd; mixed oak woods. 1 of 2
occurrences of *Galax* known in the College Woods as of
1990.
